 2009\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|[[Echo Arena Liverpool|Echo Arena]], [[Liverpool]], England}}\n|\n|-\n|10\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|10\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} Nick Okoth\n|TKO\n|3 (8)\n|18 Sep 2009\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|Marriott Hotel [[Grosvenor Square]], London, England}}\n|\n|-\n|9\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|9\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} Mathew Ellis\n|TKO\n|4 (6), {{small|0:37}}\n|15 May 2009\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|[[Odyssey (Belfast)|Odyssey Arena]], [[Belfast]], Northern Ireland}}\n|\n|-\n|8\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|8\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} Phil Goodwin\n|KO\n|2 (4), {{small|1:49}}\n|12 Dec 2008\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|Kingsway Leisure Centre, [[Widnes]], England}}\n|\n|-\n|7\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|7\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|LAT}} Jevg\u0113\u0146ijs Andrejevs\n|PTS\n|4\n|10 Oct 2008\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|Everton Park Sports Centre, [[Liverpool]], England}}\n|\n|-\n|6\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|6\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|ZIM}} Hastings Rasani\n|TKO\n|1 (4), {{small|1:52}}\n|6 Sep 2008\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|[[Manchester Arena]], [[Manchester]], England}}\n|\n|-\n|5\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|5\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|GHA}} Ayitey Powers\n|PTS\n|4\n|10 Jul 2008\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|Goresbrook Leisure Centre, [[London]], England}}\n|\n|-\n|4\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|4\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} Paul Bonson\n|{{abbr|PTS|Points decision}}\n|4\n|5 Apr 2008\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|Bolton Arena, Bolton, England}}\n|\n|-\n|3\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|3\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} Wayne Brooks\n|{{abbr|KO|Knockout}}\n|3 (4), {{small|3:00}}\n|8 Dec 2007\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|[[Bolton Arena]], [[Bolton]], England}}\n|\n|-\n|2\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|2\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} Adam Wilcox\n|TKO\n|3 (4), {{small|1:56}}\n|3 Nov 2007\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|[[Millennium Stadium]], [[Cardiff]], Wales}}\n|\n|-\n|1\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|1\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} Jamie Ambler\n|{{abbr|TKO|Technical knockout}}\n|2 (4), {{small|1:00}}\n|6 Oct 2007\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|[[Nottingham Arena]], [[Nottingham]], England}}\n|\n|}\n\n==Filmography==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class = \"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Creed (film)|Creed]]''\n| \"Pretty\" Ricky Conlan\n| \n|}\n\n==UK pay-per-view bouts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Date !! Fight !! Network !! [[Pay-per-view]] buys !! Source\n|-\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2014|Nov|22}}\n| Tony Bellew vs. Nathan Cleverly II\n| Sky Box Office\n| \n|\n|-\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2017|March|4}}\n| David Haye vs. Tony Bellew\n| Sky Box Office\n| 1,515,000\n| <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.givemesport.com/1038905-anthony-joshua-to-receive-substantial-payday-for-wladimir-klitschko-fight|title=The staggering amount Joshua will pocket from Klitschko fight [Sun]|date=2017-04-26|work=GiveMeSport|access-date=2018-05-12}}</ref><ref name=\"WBN\">{{cite news |last1=Jay |first1=Phil |title=Joshua vs Klitschko UK PPV record |url=https://www.worldboxingnews.net/2020/01/05/joshua-klitschko-ppv-record-obliterated/ |accessdate=10 January 2020 |work=World Boxing News |date=5 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2018|May|5}}\n| Tony Bellew vs. David Haye II  \n| Sky Box Office\n| 1,048,000\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Weekly viewing summary (Sky Box Office Events buys between 30 April 2018 and 6 May 2018)|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/weekly-viewing-summary/|website=[[Broadcasters' Audience Research Board]]|accessdate=2 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"WBN\" />\n|-\n| {{dts|format